WEBVTT

00:00:10.360 --> 00:00:13.900
My name is Ron Okamoto,
and I'm really happy to welcome you to

00:00:13.900 --> 00:00:16.950
this year's State of the Union for the
games industry and the games market,

00:00:17.050 --> 00:00:17.890
Mac games market.

00:00:17.900 --> 00:00:20.940
It's going to be really
interesting today.

00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:24.180
What we're going to do is we're going
to talk a little bit about Mac games,

00:00:24.180 --> 00:00:27.150
what's been happening on the platform,
and we're also going to get into some

00:00:27.150 --> 00:00:29.880
things about some trends that we see,
two things that we think

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:31.280
will be important for you.

00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:36.130
And we'll also be talking about
some ways to get your games done.

00:00:36.140 --> 00:00:38.620
And when we're all, you know,
done with looking at them,

00:00:38.620 --> 00:00:40.100
figuring out what's
going on with the market,

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:42.300
we'll then tell you maybe
even how to get published.

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:44.700
So that's the ground that we
want to cover this afternoon.

00:00:44.700 --> 00:00:47.390
So let me start off by something
that I think all of you

00:00:47.390 --> 00:00:50.010
guys are very well aware of,
which is the Mac market

00:00:50.100 --> 00:00:51.770
itself is booming right now.

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.110
You can take a look at
the revenue trends there.

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:55.830
It's been really strong for us.

00:00:55.860 --> 00:00:58.250
But what I think is important
for all of us here is,

00:00:58.250 --> 00:01:02.220
if you stand back and think about it,
a lot of people have been saying, well,

00:01:02.220 --> 00:01:05.760
gee, that's a lot of iPod revenue,
that's a lot of iTunes revenue.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:07.540
You know, what's happening with the Mac?

00:01:07.540 --> 00:01:09.580
What's happening with the things
that's running your games?

00:01:09.880 --> 00:01:11.870
Well, if we take a look at that,
let's look at volume.

00:01:11.880 --> 00:01:15.670
So here you have 2003, 4,
and 5 showing the steady growth

00:01:15.670 --> 00:01:17.220
that we had in Mac volume.

00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:20.590
But look what happens when
I lay 2006 on top of it.

00:01:20.640 --> 00:01:22.420
You can see it's been really strong.

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:26.070
And Steve mentioned to you the strong
sales and the strong unit growth

00:01:26.070 --> 00:01:30.000
that we've had in our Intel-based
portables over the last year as well.

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:33.620
So what's great for you guys is
that we think there's a fantastic

00:01:33.620 --> 00:01:37.440
opportunity now for the Mac and gaming
because the volumes were up and we

00:01:37.490 --> 00:01:39.080
know that people want to play games.

00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:43.520
But the other thing that they do is
they also want native applications.

00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:48.110
They want platform experiences and
things that really take advantage

00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:50.280
of what makes a Mac app a Mac app.

00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:53.180
And, you know, that's really what this
whole week's dedicated to.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.050
And we're going to get
really deep into that.

00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:56.680
But we want to just let you know,
you know,

00:01:56.690 --> 00:01:59.180
there's some developers out there who
have been doing really great jobs.

00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:01.040
I mean, there's a lot of you
guys doing a great job.

00:02:01.120 --> 00:02:02.550
But two that come to mind.

00:02:02.560 --> 00:02:04.370
One, for example, is Microsoft.

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:07.240
When Microsoft introduced their
most current version of Office,

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:08.980
they used a lot of really cool things.

00:02:09.110 --> 00:02:12.110
Like transparency, Aqua, OpenGL,
and some stuff to make

00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:13.360
their app look great.

00:02:13.390 --> 00:02:15.980
And they have been having
fantastic business on it.

00:02:15.980 --> 00:02:19.110
In fact, within Microsoft,
they're considered one of the stars

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:21.220
of business performance for last year.

00:02:21.530 --> 00:02:23.920
Another great developer is
Delicious Monster and their

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:25.480
Delicious Library product.

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:29.080
You know, Will Shipley has integrated
EyeSight camera functionality

00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:31.570
into his application,
really taking advantage of

00:02:31.570 --> 00:02:34.160
some of the things that we
provide with the baseline Mac.

00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:37.630
And we think that's another
opportunity for you because,

00:02:37.630 --> 00:02:40.010
for example,
if you take a look at what we're doing

00:02:40.010 --> 00:02:43.740
with all of our applications in general,
all third parties in general,

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:45.240
it's been really strong.

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:48.300
A half billion dollars
sold only in our channel,

00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:51.640
only in our retail channel
over the last year.

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:53.740
So that's a lot of products moving.

00:02:53.870 --> 00:02:57.510
And if we click down underneath that,
you can see that games is the number one

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.340
volume category in our retail stores.

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:02.350
Now, this is just our stores.

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:04.600
That's not everybody else
out there that's distributing

00:03:04.650 --> 00:03:05.820
and selling Mac products.

00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:08.520
So again,
one thing I really want to make clear is,

00:03:08.620 --> 00:03:12.140
the games and Mac go
together extremely well,

00:03:12.140 --> 00:03:13.160
and it's extremely strong.

00:03:13.160 --> 00:03:16.710
And in fact,
sales are up 10% by revenue this year.

00:03:16.970 --> 00:03:21.040
So again, these are pointing to a really,
really strong trend toward

00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:24.540
what's happening with us today,
games on the Mac.

00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:27.180
Now, another thing,
another way of measuring that

00:03:27.180 --> 00:03:29.440
interest is taking a look at how
are people looking for these.

00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.680
So for example,
if you look at our Apple store,

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:33.520
we search for everything, right?

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:36.980
People are looking for iPod accessories,
they're looking for, you know,

00:03:36.980 --> 00:03:39.620
bags for their new MacBook,
and things like that.

00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:41.380
Oh, I went a little too fast there.

00:03:41.380 --> 00:03:42.380
Sorry, guys.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:46.820
Anyway, it is within the top five of all
the searches that are going on.

00:03:46.980 --> 00:03:50.160
And these are millions of
searches that are happening today.

00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:53.720
So one thing I want to make clear
for everybody is that what's

00:03:53.720 --> 00:03:57.980
happening here is that we've noticed,
and we know, that our Mac customers are

00:03:57.980 --> 00:04:00.560
rewarding developers for a
great platform experience.

00:04:00.710 --> 00:04:03.510
And what applies to Office and
Delicious Monster applies

00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:04.570
to games as well.

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:07.040
So Mac customers want native games.

00:04:07.190 --> 00:04:09.630
And right now, today,
we have some efforts going on there.

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:14.240
So for example, Universal Binaries,
a really big thing that

00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:16.080
we introduced last year.

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:19.420
And we have to tell you,
the games community was one of the

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:21.320
fastest to jump on top of that.

00:04:21.320 --> 00:04:23.460
So here we are today,
a little over a year

00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:27.390
since we announced it,
212 days since we shipped

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:28.600
our first machine.

00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:31.260
And take a look at some of the
great titles that are out there now.

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:35.990
Shipping Universal today, Aspire,
Blizzard, a lot of our great partners

00:04:35.990 --> 00:04:38.900
have been doing a good job on
moving to Universal Binaries.

00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:40.200
And we want to thank you for that.

00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:43.390
But it's not just what's happening
with these kind of titles as well.

00:04:43.580 --> 00:04:45.270
There's international involvement now.

00:04:45.480 --> 00:04:48.470
There are some really interesting
things going on overseas.

00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:52.020
And I want to show you one here
that we're particularly fond of.

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:54.360
