but our penetration isn't nearly

00:05:50.520 --> 00:05:52.200
what it is for Linux and Windows.

00:05:52.200 --> 00:05:54.210
And so when I asked the guy, I said,
"Well, that's interesting.

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:57.040
How come this guy,
this student looks at me

00:05:57.040 --> 00:06:00.390
like I'm crazy and says,
'Well, because it's cooler.'" And so,

00:06:00.390 --> 00:06:02.270
you know,
if you have that kind of resonance

00:06:02.350 --> 00:06:04.360
going on worldwide right now,
again,

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:07.820
we think not only are we doing great
things with our major developers,

00:06:07.870 --> 00:06:08.790
but there's a seed here.

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:11.800
There's inspiration going on
for student developers as well.

00:06:11.910 --> 00:06:15.520
And of course, there you go,
Animal Kingdom by Ben.

00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:19.140
And of course, we got AAA titles,
things like Worlds of Warcraft,

00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:20.340
which has been fantastic.

00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:23.580
I mean, these guys were one of the
first to come out on universals,

00:06:23.580 --> 00:06:25.580
and they've been having huge success.

00:06:25.580 --> 00:06:28.340
Look at that, they got six and a half
million users today.

00:06:28.340 --> 00:06:31.260
And a good, you know, not a good portion,
but there's a strong number

00:06:31.260 --> 00:06:32.580
in there that's Mac users.

00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:35.900
In fact, I dare say, you know,
some of you out in the audience could

00:06:35.910 --> 00:06:37.940
probably count yourself in that group.

00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:41.800
So again, there's an example of what's
happening with Mac development today,

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:44.720
we got the universal binaries,
we have student developers,

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:47.730
we have AAA titles,
all happening right now.

00:06:47.820 --> 00:06:49.040
So that's what's going on right now.

