and where things are moving,

00:49:36.790 --> 00:49:39.120
an audio equivalent will be rendered.

00:49:39.300 --> 00:49:43.200
And you can use that to represent that
and sent through two or more channels.

00:49:43.200 --> 00:49:45.480
And the actual API is
modeled after OpenGL.

00:49:45.480 --> 00:49:48.600
And so it's really conceptually
easy for developers to pick up

00:49:48.600 --> 00:49:50.400
